We are in a situation
that is beyond morality. Hm?

497
00:58:46,310 --> 00:58:49,010
Your wife is dead.

498
00:58:49,510 --> 00:58:54,810
How do you know? How can you be definitive
about a construct you do not understand?

499
00:58:55,210 --> 00:58:57,810
She's a copy. A facsimile.

500
00:58:58,110 --> 00:59:01,310
And she's seducing you all over again.

501
00:59:01,710 --> 00:59:05,410
You're sick.

502
00:59:08,910 --> 00:59:13,110
We are not taking her back with us.

503
01:00:26,810 --> 01:00:30,510
Leave the light off.

504
01:00:42,410 --> 01:00:46,110
You think you're dreaming me.

505
01:00:46,510 --> 01:00:48,410
You're not Gibarian.

506
01:00:48,810 --> 01:00:51,310
No?

507
01:00:51,710 --> 01:00:54,710
Who am I, then?

508
01:00:55,110 --> 01:00:57,710
- A puppet.
- And you're not?

509
01:00:58,010 --> 01:01:00,410
Well, maybe you're my puppet.

510
01:01:00,710 --> 01:01:04,310
But like all puppets,
you think you're actually human.

511
01:01:04,710 --> 01:01:09,210
That's the puppet's dream - being human.

512
01:01:14,610 --> 01:01:17,310
Why did you kill yourself?

513
01:01:17,610 --> 01:01:21,310
It seemed like a good idea
at the time. Now I think I made a mistake.

514
01:01:21,810 --> 01:01:26,010
- What about your son?
- That's not my son. My son is on Earth.

515
01:01:26,410 --> 01:01:32,710
And that's not your wife.
They are part of Solaris. Remember that.

516
01:01:36,410 --> 01:01:39,210
What does Solaris want from us?

517
01:01:39,610 --> 01:01:42,910
Why do you think it has to want something?

518
01:01:43,310 --> 01:01:48,910
This is why you have to leave.
If you keep thinking there is a solution...

519
01:01:49,310 --> 01:01:51,710
you'll die here.

520
01:01:52,010 --> 01:01:54,610
I can't leave her.

521
01:01:54,810 --> 01:01:57,410
I'll figure it out.

522
01:01:57,710 --> 01:02:00,510
Do you understand
what I'm trying to tell you?

523
01:02:00,910 --> 01:02:03,210
There are no answers.

524
01:02:03,510 --> 01:02:07,210
Only choices.

525
01:02:26,810 --> 01:02:30,110
Rheya?

526
01:02:36,010 --> 01:02:39,310
Rheya?

527
01:02:50,510 --> 01:02:53,710
Rheya?

528
01:03:11,810 --> 01:03:15,110
Rheya?

529
01:03:21,510 --> 01:03:24,910
Gordon!

530
01:04:05,210 --> 01:04:10,210
- What happened?
- She drank liquid oxygen.

531
01:04:33,910 --> 01:04:37,410
She's dead.

532
01:04:38,210 --> 01:04:41,010
No.

533
01:05:02,110 --> 01:05:08,410
I never get used to them.
These... resurrections.

534
01:06:07,110 --> 01:06:10,510
Oh, no.

535
01:06:11,310 --> 01:06:14,510
No.

536
01:06:20,010 --> 01:06:23,810
Why'd you do that?

537
01:06:24,810 --> 01:06:26,010
Rheya?

538
01:06:26,310 --> 01:06:30,210
Don't call me that.

539
01:06:37,510 --> 01:06:40,110
<i>There are two components.</i>

540
01:06:40,410 --> 01:06:46,310
A high-energy proton accelerator
and a matter phase modulator.

541
01:06:46,810 --> 01:06:52,610
By adjusting the tuning frequency I get an
enhancement of Higgs antibosons at 90GHz

542
01:06:53,110 --> 01:06:57,010
and an almost pure beam at 160GHz.

543
01:06:57,410 --> 01:07:01,210
I used it on mine.

544
01:07:01,710 --> 01:07:03,410
What happens?

545
01:07:03,810 --> 01:07:08,610
They disappear,
back where they came from.

546
01:07:12,010 --> 01:07:15,710
It's what she wants.

547
01:07:16,310 --> 01:07:20,210
I won't let her do it.

548
01:07:20,510 --> 01:07:24,910
She'll come to me when you're asleep.

549
01:07:26,710 --> 01:07:30,710
Then I won't sleep.

550
01:07:32,710 --> 01:07:35,510
<i>Don't you see?
I came from your memory of her.</i>

551
01:07:35,910 --> 01:07:39,910
<i>That's the problem. I'm not a whole person.</i>

552
01:07:40,310 --> 01:07:44,810
In your memory
you get to control everything.

553
01:07:45,110 --> 01:07:49,710
So even if you remember something wrong,
I am predetermined to carry it out.

554
01:07:50,110 --> 01:07:52,510
I'm suicidal because
that's how you remember me.

555
01:07:52,810 --> 01:07:57,110
My voice sounds the way it does
because that's how you remember it.

556
01:07:57,610 --> 01:08:01,710
I don't believe that we're
predetermined to relive our past.

557
01:08:02,210 --> 01:08:06,410
I think that we can choose to do it differently.

558
01:08:06,810 --> 01:08:13,310
The day I left and you said you wouldn't make
it, I didn't hear you because I was angry.

559
01:08:13,910 --> 01:08:17,410
This is my chance to undo that mistake.

560
01:08:17,710 --> 01:08:20,110
And I need you to help me.

561
01:08:20,510 --> 01:08:24,710
But am I really Rheya?

562
01:08:28,310 --> 01:08:31,210
I don't know any more.

563
01:08:31,510 --> 01:08:35,910
All I see is you.

564
01:09:07,610 --> 01:09:11,410
All I see is you.

565
01:09:19,410 --> 01:09:23,010
It created me.

566
01:09:23,510 --> 01:09:27,810
And yet I can't communicate with it.

567
01:09:29,510 --> 01:09:32,110
It must hear me, though.

568
01:09:32,410 --> 01:09:36,710
It must know what's happening to me.

569
01:09:37,110 --> 01:09:41,210
And you and I, we would
have to have some kind of...

570
01:09:41,610 --> 01:09:45,710
an arrangement, some kind of...

571
01:09:49,310 --> 01:09:52,910
unspoken understanding...

572
01:09:53,210 --> 01:09:57,310
that I'm not really a human being.

573
01:09:59,410 --> 01:10:02,810
No, Rheya.

574
01:10:07,010 --> 01:10:08,910
Chris...

575
01:10:09,310 --> 01:10:13,310
Chris, I wish you would just
let them use the device on me.

576
01:10:13,710 --> 01:10:21,110
And then you can go back to Earth
and you can tell everybody all about Solaris.

577
01:10:23,410 --> 01:10:25,410
No.

578
01:10:25,710 --> 01:10:30,610
It's the only solution that makes any sense.

579
01:10:31,110 --> 01:10:35,110
We could never have
a life together on Earth, Chris.

580
01:10:35,510 --> 01:10:38,910
You know that.

581
01:10:39,210 --> 01:10:42,210
It would be impossible.

582
01:10:42,710 --> 01:10:46,810
And this? What kind of life is this?

583
01:10:47,210 --> 01:10:48,910
Trapped here.

584
01:10:49,310 --> 01:10:52,510
It's not a life.

585
01:10:52,910 --> 01:10:55,410
I don't know what to call it.

586
01:10:55,710 --> 01:10:59,010
It's what we have.

587
01:10:59,410 --> 01:11:01,410
It's enough for me.

588
01:11:01,710 --> 01:11:04,310
You need to rest.

589
01:11:04,710 --> 01:11:08,510
You're going to make yourself ill.

590
01:11:08,910 --> 01:11:14,210
- I don't care.
- Just lie down for a moment.

591
01:11:14,810 --> 01:11:16,510
Please, Chris.

592
01:11:16,810 --> 01:11:20,410
You have to rest.

593
01:11:49,410 --> 01:11:53,510
You know I'm not human
so I don't understand what you're afraid of.

594
01:11:54,010 --> 01:11:56,210
Of course you can use the device.

595
01:11:56,610 --> 01:11:59,810
It's not murder. You said that yourself.

596
01:12:00,210 --> 01:12:03,610
You're the one who had
the idea in the first place.

597
01:12:04,110 --> 01:12:08,110
Chris doesn't trust me. He...

598
01:17:01,010 --> 01:17:06,110
<i>Chris, don't blame Gordon.</i>

599
01:17:07,110 --> 01:17:11,510
<i>It's not her fault. I begged her to do it.</i>

600
01:17:12,510 --> 01:17:15,510
<i>It's better this way.</i>

601
01:17:16,010 --> 01:17:18,910
<i>I found the suicide note.</i>

602
01:17:19,210 --> 01:17:22,210
<i>I went through your things.</i>

603
01:17:22,510 --> 01:17:26,610
<i>The page torn from the book of poems.</i>

604
01:17:27,010 --> 01:17:30,810
<i>And I realised...</i>

605
01:17:31,110 --> 01:17:32,810
<i>I'm not her.</i>

606
01:17:33,210 --> 01:17:36,610
<i>I'm not Rheya.</i>

607
01:17:36,810 --> 01:17:39,710
<i>I know you loved me, though.</i>

608
01:17:40,110 --> 01:17:43,310
<i>I know that. I felt that.</i>

609
01:17:43,710 --> 01:17:46,110
<i>And I love you.</i>

610
01:17:46,510 --> 01:17:51,610
<i>I wish we could just
live inside that feeling forever.</i>

611
01:17:52,510 --> 01:17:56,410
<i>Maybe there's a place where we can.</i>

612
01:17:56,810 --> 01:17:58,910
<i>But I know it's not on Earth.</i>

613
01:17:59,210 --> 01:18:03,110
<i>And it's not on this ship.</i>

614
01:18:04,710 --> 01:18:08,610
<i>That's all I can say right now.</i>

615
01:18:30,510 --> 01:18:31,910
- You killed her!
- Not her. It.

616
01:18:32,210 --> 01:18:35,910
- It's murder!
- Kelvin, she begged me. It wasn't painful.

617
01:18:36,210 --> 01:18:37,510
- She'll be back!
- No.

618
01:18:37,810 --> 01:18:40,410
- Why would you let her do it?!
- Kelvin!

619
01:18:40,710 --> 01:18:42,510
It's not human!

620
01:18:42,810 --> 01:18:47,110
Whatever it is, it's not human,
and I'm threatened by that.

621
01:18:47,510 --> 01:18:50,210
And I wanna win. I want humans to win.

622
01:18:50,510 --> 01:18:54,310
Whose side are you on?

623
01:18:54,610 --> 01:19:01,110
- What are you doing?
- Putting the Al back online. I'm going home.

624
01:19:14,910 --> 01:19:18,210
Gordon.

625
01:19:19,610 --> 01:19:22,910
Gordon!

626
01:19:46,410 --> 01:19:49,810
- I knew it.
- How long you think he's been dead?

627
01:19:50,310 --> 01:19:54,710
Hard to say because of the cold.

628
01:19:55,010 --> 01:19:58,710
He attacked me.

629
01:20:00,310 --> 01:20:03,610
There I am. Somehow, there I am.

630
01:20:03,910 --> 01:20:09,410
And I couldn't tell you how I'm there,
or who I am or what's going on.

631
01:20:10,010 --> 01:20:13,310
But before I can get to that,

632
01:20:13,710 --> 01:20:15,810
what's this over here?

633
01:20:16,210 --> 01:20:19,610
Comin' at me. What...
what are you tryin' to do?

634
01:20:20,010 --> 01:20:23,010
Oh, I see. You're tryin' to kill me.

635
01:20:23,310 --> 01:20:27,210
Yeah, confusing. I'll tell you somethin'
confusing. Bingo, there you are,

636
01:20:27,610 --> 01:20:31,110
and my welcoming committee
dropped his knife and it's good night.

637
01:20:31,510 --> 01:20:35,710
And, oh, by the way, after all that I find, uh...

638
01:20:36,010 --> 01:20:40,610
this, uh, whoever this... I get my first
good look at it and it happens to be...

639
01:20:41,110 --> 01:20:44,010
I survive the first 30 seconds of this...

640
01:20:44,310 --> 01:20:48,110
life, whatever you wanna call it...
by killing someone.

641
01:20:48,510 --> 01:20:53,810
And, oh, ah, by killing someone
who happens to be me.

642
01:20:54,010 --> 01:20:58,910
See, most people... I would think most people
in this position would be, like "This... ah."

643
01:20:59,310 --> 01:21:03,810
"I don't know." However, this is at least...
This is an incredible opportunity.

644
01:21:04,310 --> 01:21:07,810
This is... What if this is a gift? I'm a gift.

645
01:21:08,210 --> 01:21:11,710
Hey.

646
01:21:13,910 --> 01:21:18,210
I say we use the Higgs device on him.

647
01:21:21,810 --> 01:21:24,110
Mm. Mm-mm.

648
01:21:24,410 --> 01:21:29,010
I don't think you really have time.

649
01:21:29,510 --> 01:21:33,210
Why would you say that?

650
01:21:33,510 --> 01:21:36,810
Well, you know, ever since
we used the famous Higgs device,

651
01:21:37,110 --> 01:21:42,010
Solaris started taking on mass exponentially.

652
01:21:42,410 --> 01:21:46,610
You might have noticed
how we're a lot closer to it.

653
01:21:46,910 --> 01:21:50,910
That would be because everything
within its gravitational field -

654
01:21:51,310 --> 01:21:55,210
it's pulling it in.

655
01:21:55,910 --> 01:21:58,010
Ah, and, yeah, sorry. By the way,

656
01:21:58,410 --> 01:22:04,410
the Higgs device also
drained the fuel cell reactors.

657
01:22:08,410 --> 01:22:12,210
Uh, if... Can I make a suggestion?

658
01:22:12,610 --> 01:22:17,410
I mean, this is... You can do what you want,
but I would just lock me in here really tight

659
01:22:17,810 --> 01:22:21,910
and take the "Athena" back.

660
01:22:24,510 --> 01:22:28,410
Wear your seat belt.

661
01:23:25,610 --> 01:23:28,010
Switch to internal power.

662
01:23:28,410 --> 01:23:31,710
Start fuel cell operational diagnostic.

663
01:23:32,010 --> 01:23:34,910
Service check on LGA.

664
01:23:35,310 --> 01:23:38,310
Point and calibrate high-beam antenna.

665
01:23:38,610 --> 01:23:42,110
Depressurising. Spin all turbines to standby.

666
01:23:42,610 --> 01:23:45,910
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

667
01:23:46,210 --> 01:23:51,010
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

668
01:24:07,610 --> 01:24:10,110
<i>Earth.</i>

669
01:24:10,410 --> 01:24:14,110
<i>Even the word sounded strange to me now.</i>

670
01:24:14,610 --> 01:24:18,010
<i>Unfamiliar.</i>

671
01:24:20,410 --> 01:24:23,410
<i>How long had I been gone?</i>

672
01:24:23,910 --> 01:24:26,910
<i>How long had I been back?</i>

673
01:24:27,310 --> 01:24:30,910
<i>Did it matter?</i>

674
01:24:34,310 --> 01:24:39,610
<i>I tried to find the rhythm
of the world where I used to live.</i>

675
01:24:40,010 --> 01:24:42,810
<i>I followed the current.</i>

676
01:24:43,310 --> 01:24:47,010
<i>I was silent and attentive.</i>

677
01:24:47,310 --> 01:24:50,910
<i>I made a conscious effort to smile...</i>

678
01:24:51,310 --> 01:24:53,210
<i>nod...</i>

679
01:24:53,610 --> 01:24:55,910
<i>stand...</i>

680
01:24:56,210 --> 01:25:02,510
<i>and perform the millions of gestures
that constitute life on Earth.</i>

681
01:25:04,310 --> 01:25:10,010
<i>I studied these gestures
until they became reflexes again.</i>

682
01:25:11,710 --> 01:25:14,310
<i>But I was haunted by the idea</i>

683
01:25:14,810 --> 01:25:18,710
<i>that I remembered her wrong.</i>

684
01:25:21,110 --> 01:25:25,510
<i>That somehow I was wrong about everything.</i>

685
01:26:29,110 --> 01:26:33,910
Depressurising.
Spin all turbines to standby.

686
01:26:34,310 --> 01:26:38,110
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

687
01:26:38,510 --> 01:26:43,310
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

688
01:27:46,610 --> 01:27:49,110
Rheya!

689
01:27:56,910 --> 01:28:00,310
Rheya?

690
01:30:13,410 --> 01:30:16,910
Chris?

691
01:30:17,310 --> 01:30:20,610
Chris?

692
01:31:00,310 --> 01:31:04,610
Am I alive... or dead?

693
01:31:07,010 --> 01:31:11,410
We don't have to think like that any more.

694
01:31:14,210 --> 01:31:18,010
We're together now.

695
01:31:19,310 --> 01:31:23,310
Everything we've done is forgiven.

696
01:31:23,710 --> 01:31:27,010
Everything.

